The paper introduces a new task of acoustic question answering (AQA) and proposes a data generation paradigm adapted from CLEVR, which is a dataset for compositional language and visual reasoning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper involves language generation and understanding. The paper also involves machine learning models and data generation, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
